stylometry: Decision trees are important in problem solving because they help us find the best positive monetary values and probabilities of a certain product or situation.  Decision tree will give as many different branches that you want it to depending on how many different catergories you are using.  In Ruby Tuesday's case I wish they would have done a decision tree to help the compnay figure out if it would be a good idea to start serving brunch on Sundays or not at a certain time throughout the day.  They should have done some type of test market much like acme did with trying to advertise internationally.
